  "read": "The MBS2 -> MBS8 drop is real enough to demote the Qwen TurboEP MBS8 row from clean scaling evidence. The configs line up, but MBS8 runs near the allocator cliff: it logs 45 CUDA memory allocation retry warnings and reaches 277.96 GiB peak, while MBS1/MBS2/MBS4 log zero retry warnings. MBS8 has high bursts but several slow steps, so the retained average is contaminated by memory/headroom and adapter-pressure effects. The old MBS4 read in this audit was superseded by torchtitan_qwen397b_primus_turbo_mbs2_mbs4_rerun_profile_20260612.json, where a clean rerun reaches 15745.63 tok/GPU/s over steps 2-20.",
